Document: MultiplayerSynchronizer
Path: godot/classes/class_multiplayersynchronizer.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the MultiplayerSynchronizer node, which controls network synchronization of properties.

Property Descriptions:
delta_interval (float): Time interval between delta synchronizations. Used when the replication is set to SceneReplicationConfig.REPLICATION_MODE_ON_CHANGE. If set to 0.0 (the default), delta synchronizations happen every network process frame.
  Method: set_delta_interval(value: float)
  Method: get_delta_interval() → float

public_visibility (bool): Whether synchronization should be visible to all peers by default. See set_visibility_for and add_visibility_filter for ways of configuring fine-grained visibility options. Default: true
  Method: set_visibility_public(value: bool)
  Method: is_visibility_public() → bool

replication_config (SceneReplicationConfig): Resource containing which properties to synchronize.
  Method: set_replication_config(value: SceneReplicationConfig)
  Method: get_replication_config() → SceneReplicationConfig

replication_interval (float): Time interval between synchronizations. Used when the replication is set to SceneReplicationConfig.REPLICATION_MODE_ALWAYS. If set to 0.0 (the default), synchronizations happen every network process frame.
  Method: set_replication_interval(value: float)
  Method: get_replication_interval() → float

root_path (NodePath): Node path that replicated properties are relative to. If root_path was spawned by a MultiplayerSpawner, the node will be also be spawned and despawned based on this synchronizer visibility options. Default: NodePath("..")
  Method: set_root_path(value: NodePath)
  Method: get_root_path() → NodePath

visibility_update_mode (VisibilityUpdateMode): Specifies when visibility filters are updated. Default: 0
  Method: set_visibility_update_mode(value: VisibilityUpdateMode)
  Method: get_visibility_update_mode() → VisibilityUpdateMode
