Document: MultiplayerSynchronizer
Path: godot/classes/class_multiplayersynchronizer.rst
Summary: This section details the methods available for managing peer visibility within a MultiplayerSynchronizer node.

Method: add_visibility_filter(filter: Callable)
Adds a peer visibility filter for this synchronizer. The filter should take a peer ID (int) and return a bool.

Method: get_visibility_for(peer: int) -> bool
Queries the current visibility for peer.

Method: remove_visibility_filter(filter: Callable)
Removes a peer visibility filter from this synchronizer.

Method: set_visibility_for(peer: int, visible: bool)
Sets the visibility of peer to visible. If peer is 0, the value of public_visibility will be updated instead.

Method: update_visibility(for_peer: int = 0)
Updates the visibility of for_peer according to visibility filters. If for_peer is 0 (the default), all peers' visibilties are updated.